text: Dean Heil is an amateur wrestler from Brunswick, Ohio. ==High school career== At St. Edward High School (Lakewood, Ohio) he was a four-time OHSAA champion at four different weight classes while wrestling for Greg Urbas. He was also 2011 champion at the Walsh Ironman. ==College career== ===2015 season=== In 2015, Heil was an All-American by virtue of finishing fourth at the 2015 NCAA Division I Wrestling Championships.Oklahoma State's Dean Heil out of title chase at NCAA Wrestling Championships | cleveland.com ===2016 season=== He won an individual title at the 2016 NCAA Division I Wrestling Championships and lost only once during that season. He defeated University of Wyoming's Bryce Meredith by a score of 3-2 in the finals. In the 2016 championships, he was a number 1 seed. ===2017 season=== Heil defended his title at the 2017 NCAA Division I Wrestling Championships, capping an undefeated season. He defeated University of Virginia's George DiCamillo 6-3 in the finals. ===2018 season=== Heil lost in the quarterfinals to eventual champion Yianni Diakomihalis of Cornell then lost his next match, finishing outside of All-American honors.Day of disappointment for Cowboy wrestling | OSU Sports | stwnewspress.com ==References== Category:Living people Category:American male sport wrestlers Category:St. Edward High School (Lakewood, Ohio) alumni Category:Oklahoma State Cowboys wrestlers Category:People from Brunswick, Ohio Category:Year of birth missing (living people)
